时报》撰稿</media:credit><media:description>前总统唐纳德·J·特朗普将他的竞选活动视为针对政治对手的“最后一战”，他和他的盟友正在制定第二任期计划，这将颠覆美国民主的一些长期准则。</media:description></item><item><title> OpenAI 员工威胁离职，危及公司未来</title><link/>https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/business/openai-staff-exodus-turmoil.html<guid ispermalink="true"> https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/business/openai-staff-exodus-turmoil.html </guid><atom:link href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/business/openai-staff-exodus-turmoil.html" rel="standout"></atom:link><description>参与罢免首席执行官萨姆·奥尔特曼 (Sam Altman) 职务的董事会成员与公司大多数员工一起呼吁推翻这一决定。</description><dc:creator>凯德·梅斯、特里普·米克尔和迈克·艾萨克</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 21 Nov 2023 00:39:14 +0000</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">人工智能</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">任命和高管变动</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">聊天GPT</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">开放人工智能实验室</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">微软公司</category><media:content height="1800" medium="image" url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/11/21/multimedia/20altJPopenai-future1-print-jphq/20openai-future-jphq-mediumSquareAt3X.jpg" width="1800"></media:content><media:credit>杰森·亨利为《纽约时报》撰稿</media:credit><media:description>OpenAI 的四人董事会周五下午早些时候解除了 Sam Altman 首席执行官的职务，称他们不再信任他，震惊了科技行业</media:description></item><item><title>微软的 Satya Nadella 如何维持 OpenAI 合作伙伴关系</title><link/>https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/technology/openai-microsoft-altman-nadella.html<guid ispermalink="true"> https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/technology/openai-microsoft-altman-nadella.html </guid><atom:link href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/technology/openai-microsoft-altman-nadella.html" rel="standout"></atom:link><description>纳德拉迅速聘请了上周五被 OpenAI 淘汰的萨姆·奥尔特曼 (Sam Altman)，并强调了他的公司在与这家人工智能初创公司的合作中所扮演的角色。</description><dc:creator>凯伦·韦斯</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 20 Nov 2023 23:43:55 +0000</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">计算机和互联网</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">人工智能</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">云计算</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">招聘和晋升</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">微软公司</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">开放人工智能实验室</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_per">塞缪尔·H·奥特曼</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_per">格雷格·布罗克曼</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_per">萨提亚·纳德拉</category><media:content height="1800" medium="image" url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/11/20/multimedia/20microsoft-openai-qmbv/20microsoft-openai-qmbv-mediumSquareAt3X.jpg" width="1800"></media:content><media:credit>伊恩·C·贝茨 (Ian C. Bates) 为《纽约时报》撰稿</media:credit><media:description>OpenAI 联合创始人萨姆·奥尔特曼（左）和微软首席执行官萨蒂亚·纳德拉于 2019 年开始合作。</media:description></item><item><title> OpenAI 的混乱 + 我们对 Sam Altman 的采访</title><link/>https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/podcasts/mayhem-at-openai-our-interview-with-sam-altman.html<guid ispermalink="true"> https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/podcasts/mayhem-at-openai-our-interview-with-sam-altman.html </guid><atom:link href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/podcasts/mayhem-at-openai-our-interview-with-sam-altman.html" rel="standout"></atom:link><description>科技界最疯狂的周末。</description><dc:creator>凯文·罗斯、凯西·牛顿、戴维斯·兰德、雷切尔·科恩、珍·波扬特、罗温·尼米斯托、丹·鲍威尔和马里昂·洛扎诺</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 21 Nov 2023 02:26:48 +0000</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">科学和技术</category><media:content height="1799" medium="image" url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/11/20/multimedia/20HF-altman-ms-gfwk/20HF-altman-ms-gfwk-mediumSquareAt3X-v3.jpg" width="1800"></media:content><media:credit>图片插图来自《纽约时报》；照片：埃里克·里斯伯格/美联社</media:credit></item><item><title>联邦法院采取行动大幅削弱投票权法案</title><link/>https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/politics/voting-rights-act.html<guid ispermalink="true"> https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/politics/voting-rights-act.html </guid><atom:link href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/politics/voting-rights-act.html" rel="standout"></atom:link><description>这项裁决几乎肯定会被上诉到最高法院，它将有效地禁止私人公民和民权团体根据这项具有里程碑意义的法律的一项关键条款提起诉讼。</description><dc:creator>尼克·科拉萨尼蒂</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 20 Nov 2023 21:19:13 +0000</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">投票权法 (1965)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">投票权、登记和要求</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">诉讼和诉讼（民事）</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">决定和判决</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">联邦法院（美国）</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">歧视</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">最高法院（美国） </category><media:content height="1800" medium="image" url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/11/20/multimedia/20pol-voting-rights-tclg/20pol-voting-rights-tclg-mediumSquareAt3X.jpg" width="1800"></media:content><media:credit>乔丹·盖尔为《纽约时报》撰稿</media:credit><media:description>投票权领导人认为最高法院目前的保守派组成对投票权法怀有敌意。</media:description></item><item><title>加沙人质家属迫切需要生还证据</title><link/>https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/politics/gaza-hostages-israel-hamas.html<guid ispermalink="true"> https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/politics/gaza-hostages-israel-hamas.html </guid><atom:link href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/politics/gaza-hostages-israel-hamas.html" rel="standout"></atom:link><description>哈马斯没有提供有关据称被关押在加沙的近 240 名人质（包括儿童）的信息。</description><dc:creator>迈克尔·D·谢尔</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 21 Nov 2023 02:12:33 +0000</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">以色列-加沙战争 (2023- )</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">绑架和人质</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">国际关系</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">人道主义援助</category><media:content height="1800" medium="image" url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/11/20/multimedia/20dc-hostages-01-vgpl/20dc-hostages-01-vgpl-mediumSquareAt3X.jpg" width="1800"></media:content><media:credit>塔米尔·卡利法 (Tamir Kalifa) 为《纽约时报》撰稿</media:credit><media:description>加沙被扣押人质的家人迫切希望获得任何信息，但他们几乎没有收到任何信息。</media:description></item><item><title>阿肯色州法律被用来镇压亲巴勒斯坦的发言者</title><link/>https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/arkansas-thrall-bds-antisemitism.html<guid ispermalink="true"> https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/arkansas-thrall-bds-antisemitism.html </guid><atom:link href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/arkansas-thrall-bds-antisemitism.html" rel="standout"></atom:link><description>为了获得适度的演讲费，学者和作家必须签署承诺，保证不参与反以色列的抵制活动。作者内森·萨尔说不，谢谢。</description><dc:creator>维马尔·帕特尔</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 21 Nov 2023 00:38:07 +0000</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">学院和大学</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">以色列-加沙战争 (2023- )</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">抵制</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">言论和表达自由</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">示威、抗议和骚乱</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">美国公民自由联盟</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">抵制、撤资和制裁 (BDS)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">阿肯色大学</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_per">萨尔，内森</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">阿肯色州</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">费耶特维尔（方舟） </category><media:content height="1800" medium="image" url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/11/17/multimedia/00nat-thrall-01-mfwb/00nat-thrall-01-mfwb-mediumSquareAt3X.jpg" width="1800"></media:content><media:credit>麦克·凯·陈（Mike Kai Chen）为《纽约时报》撰稿</media:credit><media:description>对于作家内森·萨尔（Nathan Thrall）来说，阿肯色州的法律是亲巴勒斯坦言论如何遭到系统压制的一个例子。</media:description></item><item><title> “无缘无故地浪费时间”：无人驾驶出租车如何给城市带来压力</title><link/>https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/technology/driverless-taxis-cars-cities.html<guid ispermalink="true"> https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/technology/driverless-taxis-cars-cities.html </guid><atom:link href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/technology/driverless-taxis-cars-cities.html" rel="standout"></atom:link><description>在旧金山和得克萨斯州奥斯汀，乘客可以叫车自动驾驶汽车，但这些汽车增加了城市员工的工作量。</description><dc:creator>艺文路</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 20 Nov 2023 13:47:52 +0000</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">无人驾驶和半自动车辆</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">火灾和消防员</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">交通事故与安全</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">汽车</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">事故与安全</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">汽车服务和出租车</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">运输</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">汽车安全特性和缺陷</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">计算机和互联网</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">字母表公司</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">邮轮有限责任公司</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">通用汽车</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">谷歌公司</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org">韦莫</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">奥斯汀 (德克萨斯州)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">旧金山（加利福尼亚州） </category><media:content height="1800" medium="image" url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/11/02/multimedia/DRIVERLESS-CITY-kjgm/DRIVERLESS-CITY-kjgm-mediumSquareAt3X.jpg" width="1800"></media:content><media:credit>吉姆·威尔逊/纽约时报</media:credit><media:description>八月，旧金山的一辆 Cruise 自动驾驶汽车。机器人出租车服务给城市雇员带来了越来越大的负担。</media:description></item><item><title>在死亡谷，一个罕见的湖泊复活了</title><link/>https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/death-valley-lake.html<guid ispermalink="true"> https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/death-valley-lake.html </guid><atom:link href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/us/death-valley-lake.html" rel="standout"></atom:link><description>游客通常会涌向死亡谷国家公园，感受酷热并欣赏贫瘠的景观。今年秋天，他们被一种不同的自然特征所吸引：水。</description><dc:creator>吉尔·考恩和梅特·兰普科夫</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 20 Nov 2023 19:09:39 +0000</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">国家公园、纪念碑和海岸</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">死亡谷国家公园</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">湖泊</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">水</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">加利福尼亚州</category><media:content height="1800" medium="image" url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/11/20/multimedia/20nat-death-valley-01-hwgp/20nat-death-valley-01-hwgp-mediumSquareAt3X.jpg" width="1800"></media:content></item><item><title>哈维尔·米雷的总统胜利是阿根廷的唐纳德·特朗普时刻</title><link/>https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/world/americas/javier-milei-argentina-trump.html<guid ispermalink="true"> https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/world/americas/javier-milei-argentina-trump.html </guid><atom:link href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/world/americas/javier-milei-argentina-trump.html" rel="standout"></atom:link><description>哈维尔·米雷说过，没有政府，社会会更好。现在他即将执掌阿根廷队。</description><dc:creator>杰克·尼卡斯、娜塔莉·阿尔科巴和露西娅·乔拉基安·埃雷拉</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 20 Nov 2023 21:50:10 +0000</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">政治与政府</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">经济状况和趋势</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">选举</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_per">哈维尔·米莱</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">阿根廷</category><media:content height="1800" medium="image" url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2023/11/20/multimedia/20argentina-milei-01-gplj/20argentina-milei-01-gplj-mediumSquareAt3X.jpg" width="1800"></media:content><media:credit> Juan Ignacio Roncoroni/EPA，来自 Shutterstock</media:credit><media:description>当选总统哈维尔·米莱周日在布宜诺斯艾利斯向支持者致意。 “我们国家需要的变革是巨大的，”他在胜选演讲中说道。</media:description></item><item><title>为什么我们仍然呼吸着肮脏的室内空气</title><link/>https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/health/indoor-air-covid-pollution.html<guid ispermalink="true"> https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/health/indoor-air-covid-pollution.html </guid><atom:link href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/20/health/indoor-air-covid-pollution.html" rel="standout"></atom:link><description>这场流行病和最近的野火已经表明室内空气是多么不健康。但科学和政府的惰性减缓了必要的补救措施。</description><dc:creator>阿普尔瓦·曼达维利</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 20 Nov 2023 15:12:31 +0000</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">你的饲料科学</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">冠状病毒（2019-nCoV）</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">供暖、通风和制冷 (HVAC)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/d